## Change 1: `build_controller_tf.m` (mc branch only)

Insert after line 25 (the existing `Kp_att` read):

```matlab
[Kd_att,     info] = getp(params, sprintf('MC_%s_D', ax_att), 0,   info);
[yaw_weight, info] = getp(params, 'MC_YAW_WEIGHT',            1.0, info);
```

Replace the existing `C_att` construction (lines 36-40):

```matlab
% PX4 implementation note (AttitudeControl.cpp:91-93): rate_setpoint_d = -Kd_att*rates,
% applied to the gyro-filtered rates directly with NO additional LPF. Since P_rate is
% identified from those same gyro-filtered rates, the gyro filter is already inside
% P_rate. Adding the IMU_DGYRO_CUTOFF LPF here is a numerical-convenience step that
% keeps C_att strictly proper; the response at attitude-loop frequencies is identical
% to a pure PD to <1%.
% yaw_weight (MC_YAW_WEIGHT) is recorded for reference but NOT applied — it cancels
% exactly in linearized small-signal analysis (see AttitudeControl.cpp:44-52, 81).
if isfinite(Kp_att)
    if isfinite(Kd_att) && Kd_att ~= 0
        C_att = Kp_att + Kd_att*s/(tau_d*s + 1);
    else
        C_att = tf(Kp_att, 1);
    end
else
    C_att = [];
end
```

Extend the gain bookkeeping (existing line 41-43) with:

```matlab
info.gains.Kd_att     = Kd_att;
info.gains.yaw_weight = yaw_weight;  % recorded only; cancels in linearized model
```

FW branch (lines 45-83) is untouched — no `FW_*_D` or `FW_YAW_WEIGHT` equivalent in PX4.

