## Change 4: `compare_inputs.m` — Nichols overlay

Pass `fmin_Hz`, `fmax_Hz` into `plot_overlay` (currently the helper signature is `plot_overlay(P_A, P_B, fig_dir, axis_name)` — extend to `plot_overlay(P_A, P_B, fig_dir, axis_name, fmin_Hz, fmax_Hz)` and update the single caller).

After the existing Bode `save_fig(fig, fig_dir, ['compare_' axis_name '_bode'])` call, add a second figure:

```matlab
% --- Nichols overlay (TF fits only — interpolated lines, no measured-FRF dots) ---
fig = figure('Name', ['Nichols-' axis_name], 'Visible', 'off', 'Color', 'w', ...
             'Position', [100 100 900 700]);
hold on; grid on;
w = logspace(log10(2*pi*fmin_Hz), log10(2*pi*fmax_Hz), 512).';
if ~isempty(P_A.tf)
    h = squeeze(freqresp(P_A.tf, w));
    plot(unwrap(angle(h))*180/pi, 20*log10(abs(h)), 'b-', 'LineWidth', 1.5, ...
         'DisplayName', label_A);
end
if ~isempty(P_B.tf)
    h = squeeze(freqresp(P_B.tf, w));
    plot(unwrap(angle(h))*180/pi, 20*log10(abs(h)), 'r-', 'LineWidth', 1.5, ...
         'DisplayName', label_B);
end
xlabel('Phase (deg)'); ylabel('Gain (dB)');
title(['Nichols (TF fits) — axis: ' axis_name]);
legend('Location', 'best', 'Interpreter', 'tex');
save_fig(fig, fig_dir, ['compare_' axis_name '_nichols']);
```

`label_A` / `label_B` strings are already defined just above in `plot_overlay` (`'A: torque\_setpoint\rightarrowrates  (plant P\_rate)'` and `'B: rates\_setpoint\rightarrowrates  (closed loop T\_rate)'`).

Rationale for manual plotting vs. `nichols(P.tf)`: MATLAB's `nichols` cannot be coerced to use distinct colors per call without extra options, and `nichols` doesn't accept the `'DisplayName'` argument for legends. Manual `plot(phase_deg, mag_dB)` over a chosen w-grid is cleaner and matches the "interpolated lines" the user asked for.

